ärfung und Skandalisierung waren dabei an der Tagesordnung. Sahen jedoch SED und ihr Geheimdienst in den Vertriebenenverbänden tatsächlich eine "Revanchismusgefahr" oder dienten ihre verdeckten Operationen anderen Zielen?  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHistory of Germany. 0aModern history, 1453-. 0aPolitical refugeeszGermany (East)xHistory. 0aPolitical refugeeszGermany (West)xHistory. 0aPolitical science (General). 0aSubversive activitieszGermany (East)xHistory. 4aBRD. 4aDDR. 4aMinisterium für Staatssicherheit. 4aSED. 4aVertriebenenverbände. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket OWV/AV  Geschichte 2005-2012z9783110346787oZDB-23-OGS0 cprintz978348670589840uhttps://doi.org/10.1524/9783486713343zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783486713343zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783486713343/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GHIc2000d2014  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-OGSc2005d2012